reviewText: I did not find the files in Google Drive
This course was not what I was looking for. I am unable to utilize the files or clearly see the demos. I would like to delete this course but can't figure out how to unenroll.
The first thing that caught my eye is how poorly written this course is. Then, the first step in the guided project is to learn how to create and sign into a Gmail account? I'm confused.

I appreciate what the instructor was trying to do. The information is good and she knows her stuff. However, this course is presented in a poor way. Pretty much the whole course is reviewing a Google Word Document, which has a number of misspellings. It also had a copy/paste error from Task 6 and 7 and posed the same question. The instructor should partner with a media company and make example interview videos etc. to make this more effective. Good info, but the presentation experience was poor.

I found the first section on setting  up a Gmail account confusing. The instructor obviously reading, and their own examples to course questions, didn't give me confidence in the content. The quiz was only 7 poorly worded questions with mistakes, and 2 of them were on setting up a Gmail account. Some useful content, but overall I think I could fine more tips through a Google search unfortunately.

This course is suitable for beginners but not for experienced professionals as it hardly provides any insight or incremental information that is not readily available on all similar advice offering career sites.
I love my certificate at the end, but I am confused on the how easy this course was being that it was one video and one quiz. I loved to instructor and certificate. Thank you!
This course did not provide me with a challenge. Perhaps I was not the intended audience, but rather this course was intended for someone who will be going to his or her first interview.

It would be better if there are some more details. For example, for "the home work of company research", it would be nice to point out what is important to use the company informations in your interview or coverletter.

reviewText: Very good course!!! Keep a note of the questions to be prepared from the guided project for your dream company!!! Very useful for planning for an interview.
It helped me to understand whole process of Interview from an employee as well as employer's view point.

This course was  informative and helped with what you thought you know about issues of the interviewing  progess of what you may not concern about in the interview.  Which gives you a world of knowledge of what you could miss when you go.
For me, this is the first course that I am taking in this field, but I am very optimistic. Thank you for those who contributed to the publication of this course.
It's a great course for each and everyone
